
[1]esplanade

   ESPLANA'DE, n. [L. planus, plain.]

   1. In fortification, the glacis of the counter scarp, or the sloping of
   the parapet of the covered-way towards the country; or the void space
   between the glacis of a citadel, and the first houses of the town.

   2. In gardening, a grass-plat.
